british sailors from the frigate 
avenger and a british helicopter towing a huge grenadian flag took 
part in a military parade marking this caribbean islands 15th 
anniversary of independence from britain 
premier ha blaize gov gen sir paul scoon and other 
dignitaries and opposition leaders took part in the ceremony 
attended by about 2000 people 
the tiny eastern caribbean island with a population of 100000 
people became independent from britain on feb 7 1974 
it was the scene of a usled invasion in october 1983 that 
ousted a regime of hardline marxists who days before assassinated 
leftist prime minister maurice bishop in a bloody coup 
