americans borrowed 54 billion more than they 
repaid in december the government reports 
the december borrowing raised the consumer debt at an annual rate 
of 99 percent the federal reserve board said tuesday the consumer 
debt rose 47 billion in november and increased 39 billion in 
october 
the seasonally adjusted annual rate of credit growth was 85 
percent in november and 72 percent in october 
decembers increase matched the 99 percent rise recorded last 
august which was the highest since a 152 percent increase in june 
the december jump was paced by an increase in outstanding auto 
loans while growth in the category of debt that includes credit 
cards slowed from the rapid pace of the preceding two months 
consumer spending is closely watched as a barometer of economic 
health because it accounts for twothirds of the gross national 
product 
</TEXT>
