which takes effect march 1 abandons a provision that all 
irreconcilable conflicts between smokers and nonsmokers be 
resolved in favor of nonsmokers 
the original policy on smoking was drafted last fall but never 
went into effect at the university where 22000 students are 
enrolled some legislators had threatened the university with a loss 
in state support 
weve tried to address all concerns including those of the 
legislators swain said 
there was concern within the university that smokers be treated 
with some balance we were concerned that the previous policy was a 
little onesided 
swain said the revised policy directs department heads to discuss 
and settle conflicts with employees 
the policy also drops a ban on smoking in open work areas 
directing instead that such areas be separated into smoking and 
nonsmoking areas or be designated one or the other after 
discussions with the affected employees 
