<TEXT>
the justice department interrupted oliver 
norths irancontra trial today urging new safeguards to prevent 
the former white house aide from making surprise disclosures of 
classified information 
north has made no effort to assist the court in dealing 
responsibility with classified information the department said in 
a court filing that it made on behalf of us intelligence agencies 
in the filing by assistant attorney general edward sg dennis 
the justice department asked us district judge gerhard a gesell 
to prohibit north from disclosing any classified information except 
with explicit court rulings that it is admissible and when the 
united states has no pending objection at the time the disclosure is 
made 
gesell immediately postponed the jury selection process until 
thursday and scheduled an afternoon hearing to discuss whether the 
department of justice has any business being here the trial began 
jan 31 and opening arguments had been imminent 
independent counsel lawrence walsh whose office is prosecuting 
north protested the departments intervention and made a proposal 
of his own in an attempt to overcome the agencys interference he 
proposed alternative proposals to protect classified information 
seeking an order to enable the court to proceed to trial without 
delay 
the justice department noting that walsh had sought a less 
extensive protective order than the one sought by the government 
said the attorney general not the independent counsel was the 
final arbiter of classified information issues 
whether or not the department of justice has any business being 
here has to be talked about gesell said im just a way station 
on an elevator ride upstairs he said he wanted to hear arguments 
on the right of the department of justice to participate against 
the independent counsel 
charging that north has provided totally useless or at best 
minimally informative notices of the documents he wants to 
disclose the department urged gesell to institute greater 
protections to prevent unwarranted disclosures 
a department source speaking on condition of anonymity said 
that if gesell ruled against the government it would appeal such an 
appeal could delay the trial 
the department said gesell has issued only general guidance 
on the relevance and admissability of secret information so the 
parties are left to their own devices to determine in opening 
statements direct examination and crossexamination as to what 
classified information to mention 
without specific orders the department said there is every 
reason to believe that irrelevent or immaterial classified 
information might be revealed during trial 
the department urged gesell to follow the procedures of the 
classified information procedures act known as cipa they provide 
for closed hearings on the admissibility and relevance of classified 
evidence and for the attorney general to object to disclosure on the 
ground it would damage national security 
the court can seek to resolve admissibility issues before any 
evidence is offered or it can postpone some decisions but that 
whatever the decision it must afford the government and the 
attorney general the protections of cipa the departments filing 
said 
norths obstinate refusal to participate meaningfully in cipa 
proceedings cannot undermine the right of the united states and the 
responsibility of the attorney general to protect classified 
information while assuring that cases that can be tried will be 
tried it said 
at the present time the procedures adopted by the court in the 
instant case fail to implement the most important features of 
cipa the document added 
the government would be given an opportunity to register its 
objections at closed hearings to the disclosure of any classified 
evidence the justice department said 
the filing said north a former white house national security 
aide would not need specific permission to rely on prosecution and 
defense exhibits already edited for sensitive references by an 
interagency security group 
we are prepared to work with the court to make cipa effective 
in this case the department said it is a complex case in terms 
of classified information but we believe it is not so complex that 
it cannot go forward 
but in the face of the defendants intransigence we believe it 
is important that the government have the cipa protections available 
in their fullest the department said 
walsh countered with a proposal of his own seeking an order 
enabling the court to proceed to trial without delay 
the independent counsel said he wants an order stating that the 
rules limiting disclosure for classified information apply to 
norths opening statement crossexamination and other aspects of 
the defense case 
walsh also asked for an order stating that the defense make no 
mention of certain unspecified topics in its opening statement or at 
any point in the trial without first obtaining court approval 
in addition walsh said the government will advise the defense 
in advance of a witness testimony of any classified information 
that seems especially pertinent to the witness 
the government will endeavor to keep identification of 
classified information narrow specific and reasonable he said 
north faces 12 criminal charges he is accused of allegedly 
concealing from congress in 1985 and 1986 his efforts on behalf of 
the nicaraguan contras and of covering up from the attorney general 
the national security councils role in diverting money from the 
iran arms sales to the contras 
north also is accused of illegally accepting a 13800 security 
system at his home from codefendant richard secord converting to 
his own use at least 4300 in travelers checks from contra leader 
adolfo calero and conspiring to defraud the treasury of tax revenue 
in connection with charitable contributions supporting the contras 
due to national security concerns the two central charges in the 
case against north were dismissed jan 13 
those were the conspiracy and theft counts which accuse north of 
illegally diverting more than 14 million in us iran arms sale 
proceeds to the nicaraguan rebels 
