indicated that dukakis received between 25 and 30 percent of the 
white vote there which actually was an improvement over mondales 
showing of about 20 percent 
she said her polling found that in 1981 51 percent of white 
voters in alabama identified themselves as democrats and 32 percent 
as republicans her latest survey taken in october 1988 found those 
numbers reversed with 52 percent calling themselves republicans and 
33 percent democrats 
she said that while many voters reject the democratic party 
because it has black support there are other factors which argue 
against so simplistic an analysis 
