<TEXT>
ayatollah ruhollah khomeini has pardoned 
political prisoners in iran in a general amnesty declared during 
celebrations marking the 10th anniversary of the islamic revolution 
tehran radio announced wednesday 
neither the state radio nor the official islamic republic news 
agency both monitored in nicosia specified how many prisoners 
would be freed or when the amnesty would take effect 
the state radio said khomeini proclaimed the amnesty at the 
request of intelligence minister mohammad reyshahri who said in a 
letter to the revolutionary patriarch that the political groups no 
longer constitute a threat to the revolution 
the radio said all but 900 prisoners jailed for belonging to 
outlawed opposition groups will be freed under the amnesty 
the 900 have been directly involved in crimes reyshahri 
said 
irans main opposition group the iraqibased mujahedeen khalq 
had said 140000 dissidents were arrested in recent years as 
khomeinis islamic revolution consolidated its grip on power after 
overthrowing the monarchy in 1979 
reyshahri a hardliner and soninlaw of president ali khamenei 
told khomeini he proposes all imprisoned members of the grouplets 
be pardoned regardless of the judicial stage of their cases 
irna reported 
it quoted khomeini as agreeing and hoping authorities will treat 
the pardoned prisoners kindly and in a brotherly manner and would 
encourage them by providing them with employment facilities 
khomeinis latest amnesty followed a wave of executions in which 
hundreds of political prisoners and captured antikhomeini activists 
have been reported slain 
the executions have taken place despite signs that tehran is 
moving toward easing political social and religious restrictions 
after the aug 20 ceasefire in the war with iraq 
the government has said it will allow political parties to form 
provided they do not conspire against the state 
the mujahedeen have said claimed more than 12000 iranians have 
been executed since august 
in a statement wednesday the mujahedeen called the amnesty a 
trick to gain support and called on the united nations to verify 
amnesty releases 
khomeini finds himself in dire need of an amnesty claim on the 
eve of the 10th anniversary of his faltering rule said the 
statement there is nothing but demagogery and deceit to this 
ploy 
the londonbased amnesty international which monitors human 
rights worldwide said last week that it knows of more than 1500 
executions in that period 
the us state department also criticized human rights abuses in 
iran in a report issued tuesday 
stories of torture in irans prisons are rampant and cover 
mock executions threats of sexual abuse and floggings the report 
said 
last month khomeini announced that thousands of prisoners who 
had served onethird of their sentences would be freed during the 
10th anniversary celebrations which end saturday hundreds have 
already been released 
that amnesty apparently aimed primarily at common criminals 
rather than political prisoners did not include prisoners serving 
life terms sentenced to death drug smugglers spies and hardcore 
opponents of khomeinis regime 
khomeini also suspended executions of drug smugglers during the 
10day anniversary celebrations 
at least 132 alleged drug traffickers were publicly hanged last 
month amid a ferocious antinarcotics campaign which includes a new 
law mandating death for anyone found possessing even small 
quantities of drugs 
