<TEXT>
get your tax refund fast the hightechnology way 
thats the pitch offered by increasing numbers of tax preparers 
and financial institutions trying to attract customers in the 1989 
income tax filing season 
to deliver on their promise they use the internal revenue 
services electronic filing system through which individual returns 
are filed directly by computer over telephone lines rather than 
through the mail 
last year 500000 of the approximately 107 million returns 
received by the irs were filed electronically according to wilson 
fadley an irs spokesman 
this year the service expects the number to reach 2 million 
its kind of a wave of the future fadley says 
electronic filing is available in 36 states this year through 
some 4000 irsapproved data transmitters including taxpreparation 
firms and computer service bureaus that work with banks and other 
financial institutions 
plans call for the system to operate nationwide next year at this 
time fadley says 
to find out if and where electronic filing is available in your 
state the arthur young tax guide advises inquiring at your local 
irs taxpayer service or the tollfree national information number 
18004241040 and asking for the electronic filing coordinator 
judging from several test calls made on a recent weekday morning 
getting through on the tollfree number may take patience and 
persistence 
electronic filing isnt available to individuals using their own 
personal computers though it may be someday thus you can expect 
to have to pay someone to provide it for you either in the form of 
an explicit charge or built into a tax preparers fee 
for example the dollar dry dock bank in the new york 
metropolitan area charges 45 
what are the benefits the most tangible is faster access to your 
federal tax refund especially if you have a large amount due you 
but there are other pluses as well as your return is processed 
for electronic filing any mathematical errors you may have made are 
likely to be detected 
with electronic filing you get a confirmation from the irs that 
your return has been received 
the irs likes the system too since it reduces the costs of 
processing returns 
people who owe additional taxes cant use the system as it is set 
up now if youre in this position youre probably in no rush to 
pay anyway unless you were underwithheld in 1988 by so much that 
you are threatened with penalties and interest charges 
before you deal with a bank or other financial institution that 
promotes electronic filing services investigate all the trappings 
of the arrangement 
a bank may even offer to deposit the amount of your refund on the 
spot into an account in your name 
if this involves opening a new account it makes sense to inquire 
what sort of an account it is what interest it will pay and 
whether there are any restrictions on withdrawing the money and 
closing the account 
wouldbe electronic filers might feel leery of getting involved 
in direct dealings with the irss computers the process strikes 
some people as the sort of highprofile activity that invites extra 
scrutiny from the irs and its auditors 
not so the authorities say the arthur young tax guide offers 
the solemn assurance that electronic filing neither increases nor 
decreases the possibility that your return will be audited 
