<TEXT>
the 1989 mazda 929 is a study in understated luxury and 
convenience 
its easy to see why mazda is so proud of this its flagship 
vehicle the 929s 3liter v6 an 18valve fuelinjected 
powerplant that produces up to 158 horsepower at 5500 rpm was 
smooth and flawless with the fourspeed overdrive automatic 
transmission just touch the accelerator and you felt the car pull 
itself together and zoom you were off 
the trunk lid was heavy and there was a solid thud upon closing 
the doors indicative of a solid wellbuilt car inside the 
fourdoor sedan felt roomy the optional leather seats were 
comfortable and looked plush yet elegant dashboard instruments 
were arrayed impressively over twothirds of the dash but were 
clearly marked and easy to read 
but what do you expect when you lay out 25000 in the test car 
you could expect more it had the optional feature that allows 
changes in the way the auto rides 
by touching a button on the center console the driver can select 
soft sport or automatic suspensions the soft adjustment puts front 
and rear shock absorbers at the normal setting the sport adjustment 
puts them at the firm setting and automatic adjusts their firmness 
according to the cars speed 
i preferred the sport setting and found it to be a nice 
compromise between some of the more punishing sport suspensions of 
racier cars and the floating sensation on some bigger luxury cars 
overall handling on the 929 was admirable the car felt nimble 
and maneuvered as easily as some smaller cars in tight spaces the 
test 929s transmission also could be switched from economy to power 
mode when great acceleration was needed 
