california has displaced new york as the state 
with the most multinational manufacturing companies the conference 
board said in a report released wednesday 
california now has 150 publicly owned manufacturing firms with 
offices abroad compared with 130 headquartered in new york state 
according the report by the worldwide organization of corporate 
executives 
the report is based on 1988 corporate data of the foreign 
operations of 1700 publicly held manufacturers it said there are 
990 usowned manufacturing multinationals with foreign assets of 
126 billion up from 884 in 1987 
in 1987 new york was home to 123 foreignaffiliated 
manufacturers and california had 108 
james greene an international trade specialist who compiled the 
data said the number of us multinational manufacturers has fallen 
from about 2000 in the late1970s 
since then many have been taken over by foreign firms others 
have been merged into larger multinationals and many have been 
privatized through leveraged buyouts he said these trends are 
likely to continue through the next few years concentrating 
usowned foreign assets in fewer and fewer corporate hands 
new york still has more multinational firms with annual sales of 
1 billion or more 44 compared with californias 24 but 
california has 66 multinationals with sales of 100 million or less 
compared with 34 in new york 
