cbs inc said wednesday its fourthquarter profit dropped 84 
percent from strong results a year ago that included a huge gain on 
the sale of its magazine division and that income from its 
broadcasting operations fell 37 percent 
two other media concerns posted profit gains for the quarter as 
earnings rose 19 percent at the new york times co and 77 percent at 
timesmirror co 
but the washington post co reported its fourthquarter profit 
dropped 427 percent from a year ago 
cbs said its net income fell to 401 million or 156 a share 
in the three months ended dec 31 from 2516 million or 973 a 
share in the same period in 1987 
fourthquarter revenue slipped 1 percent to 772 million from 
773 million 
the 1987 results included a 1798 million gain on the sale of 
cbs magazines 
the company said income from continuing operations rose 78 
percent to 401 million in the quarter boosted by higher interest 
income and lower corporate expenses 
but the cbs broadcast operations profit fell to 124 million 
from 198 million a year earlier 
it said the cbs television network results were depressed by the 
22week writers guild strike which delayed the start of the current 
television season and led to lower audience ratings and ad revenue 
cbs trails nbc and abc in primetime audience ratings 
cbs said its television stations and radio operations each 
reported higher sales and income for the period 
for the year cbs said it earned a record 115 billion or 
4475 a share compared with 4525 million or 1774 a share a 
year earlier 
fullyear revenue rose 1 percent to 278 billion from 276 
billion 
the fullyear results reflected a gain of 866 million on the 
sale of the cbs records division in january and interest income on 
the investment of money generated by asset sales the company had 
net interest income of 185 million in 1988 compared with a net 
interest expense of 69 million in 1987 
new york times co said its net income rose to 504 million or 
64 cents a share in the fourth quarter from 425 million or 52 
cents a share a year earlier 
fourthquarter revenue rose 3 percent to 450 million from from 
4355 million a year earlier 
for the year it said net income rose 5 percent to a record 
1677 million or 208 a share from 1603 million or 196 a 
share a year ago 
fullyear revenue rose 4 percent to 17 billion from 16 
billion in 1987 
arthur ochs sulzberger chairman and chief executive said the 
softening in some markets is likely to result in a down first 
quarter in 1989 
in addition to publishing the new york times the company has 
interests in regional newspapers magazines broadcasting and forest 
products 
timesmirror based in los angeles said it earned 968 million 
or 76 cents a share up from 547 million or 42 cents a share a 
year earlier 
fourthquarter revenue rose 69 percent to 925 million from 865 
million 
the 1988 results include a 2 million gain on sale of assets 
while the 1987 results included a pretax loss of 437 million on 
asset sales 
for the year the company said it earned 332 million or 258 a 
share up from 266 million or 206 a share a year earlier 
fullyear revenue rose to 333 billion from 314 billion a year 
ago 
the 1988 results included a 589 million gain on the sale of 
assets while the 1987 results reflected a 292 million loss on the 
sale of assets 
the company publishes newspapers including the los angeles times 
and has interests in television stations cable television 
magazines and books 
washington post co said it earned 369 million or 287 a 
share in the fourth quarter compared to 644 million or 501 per 
share a year earlier 
fourthquarter revenue rose 16 percent to 3708 million from 
365 million a year earlier 
the latest results included a 126 million charge related to a 
previouslydisclosed restructuring at newsweek while the 1987 
earnings included 235 million in onetime gains from the sale of 
cellular telephone interests 
for the year the company earned 2691 million or 2091 a 
share up 441 percent from 1867 million or 1452 a share a 
year ago 
fullyear revenue rose 4 percent to 137 billion from 132 
billion in 1987 
 
