<TEXT>
isc systems corp a manufacturer of 
automated banking systems said wednesday it has agreed to be 
acquired italys olivetti in a 174 million deal 
isc systems said that after the takeover it would be merged with 
bunker ramo corp of shelton conn a wholly owned subsidiary of 
the office automation company ing c olivetti amp co of ivrea 
italy 
olivetti offered to buy all outstanding shares of isc common 
stock at 1225 per share in cash 
isc had announced in late january that it had agreed to be 
acquired at that price but did not disclose who the buyer would be 
the deal must still be approved by isc shareholders and federal 
regulatory agencies 
in national overthecounter trading isc rose 1 a share to 
1162 
the new company which will have headquarters in spokane would 
have had revenues of about 250 million in 1988 including iscs 
175 million 
this acquisition reinforces our worldwide position in banking 
automation vittorio cassoni olivettis managing director and 
chief operating officer said in a prepared statement it greatly 
expands our market share in north america complementing our leading 
role in europe and japan 
the new company would have the thirdlargest market share among 
firms selling automated financial services systems behind 
international business machines corp and ncr corp according to 
john lindeblad president and chief operating officer of isc systems 
about 25 percent of olivettis sales of more than 6 billion in 
1988 were to the banking industry but little of that was in the 
united states said ted demerritt isc systems chairman and chief 
executive officer 
analysts who follow isc systems said the merger offers a good fit 
of companies in both domestic and international markets 
daniel nelson an analyst with ragen mackenzie in seattle said 
olivetti could gain from iscs presence in asia while isc would get 
a toehold in the european market dominated by olivetti the 
spokanebased isc which has a large share of the domestic savings 
and loan market also stands to benefit from its association with 
bunker ramos commercial banking ties he said 
there are probably some synergies involved agreed dain 
bosworth analyst william whitlow in seattle they can take isc 
software and couple it with bunker ramo hardware and tie it all into 
olivetti mainframes its probably a better package and it gives 
olivetti a better product to market 
james d lindner president and chief executive officer of bunker 
ramo will become chairman and ceo of the asyet unnamed company 
iscs lindeblad will remain as president while demerritt will become 
vice chairman 
isc systems is a leading supplier of pinnacle branch automation 
systems to savings and loans credit unions and commercial banks in 
the us it also markets its products in latin america the united 
kingdom asia and canada 
bunker ramo supplies branch automation systems mostly to 
commercial banks 
isc systems announced dec 22 it would begin discussions with a 
possible suitor the announcement coincided with a restructuring 
that could eliminate as many as 120 jobs at its spokane operations 
where 750 people were employed as of jan 1 
demerritt said the merger will mean the loss of some jobs and 
reshuffling of others the reorganization announced before the 
merger will continue he said 
isc systems spokesman wes lynch said the program expected to be 
completed by june will result in a workforce of between 630650 
people 
isc was founded in 1977 and its products serve more than 2700 
financial institutions employing 1700 worldwide 
bunker ramo which employs about 600 people in the us was 
purchased by olivetti in 1986 its systems are found in 750 
financial institutions 
